newsitem.title: CHINA: Shanghai soybeans end mixed in slow trading.
newsitem.headline: Shanghai soybeans end mixed in slow trading.

text.p: Shanghai soybean futures ended mixed in slow trading on Wednesday with most investors continuing to stay on the sidelines, traders said.
The most active September contract fell six to 3,344 yuan ($403) per tonne. It opened at 3,350, hitting an intra-day high of 3,356 and a low of 3,340.
March rose 10 to 3,110, May fell seven to 3,160, July rose 49 to 3,320, November down two to 3,350 and the January 1998 contract up two to 3,350.
Combined volume fell to 17,600 tonnes from 18,500.
Traders said most contracts moved in a narrow range for most of the session with retail investors dominating today's trade.
"The lack of institutional funds resulted in a lack of vitality on the soybeans market," one trader said.
Traders expect soybeans to move around current levels in the next few days.
